title: Khan Academy
description:
You can learn anything.
For free. For everyone. Forever.

title: Early math
description: Learn early elementary math—counting, shapes, basic addition and subtraction, and more.

title: Counting
description: Learn how to count. Say how many objects you see.

title: Counting
description: Learn to count from 0 to 20.

title: Counting with small numbers
description: Sal counts squirrels and horses.

title: Count with small numbers
description: Practice counting up to 10 objects.

title: Counting in order
description: Learn how to count without making mistakes.

title: Count in order
description: Practice counting without making mistakes.

title: Find 1 more or 1 less than a number
description: Practice finding one more or one less than a number.

title: Numbers 0 to 120
description: Learn the numbers from 0 to 120.

title: Missing numbers
description: Find the missing number in a list of numbers. Numbers used are 20 or less.

title: Number grid
description: Sal goes through all the numbers from 0 to 100 and shows some interesting patterns.

title: Missing numbers between 0 and 120
description: Sal finds missing numbers between 0 and 120.

title: Numbers to 100
description: Practice finding missing numbers in a list of numbers between 0 and 100.

title: Numbers to 120
description: Practice finding missing numbers in a list of numbers between 0 and 120.

title: Count tens
description: Practice counting by tens.

title: Counting objects
description: Learn to count up to 20 objects.

title: Counting in pictures
description: Sal counts the number of objects in pictures.

title: Count in pictures
description: Practice counting objects in pictures.

title: Counting objects 1
description: Learn to count groups of whales, sheep, and flowers.

title: Count objects 1
description: Practice counting up to 20 objects. Objects are organized neatly into rows and columns.

title: Counting objects 2
description: Learn to count dogs, mice, and cookies in random patterns.

title: Count objects 2
description: Practice counting up to 20 objects in random patterns.

title: Comparing small numbers
description: Learn to compare numbers between 0 and 10.

title: Comparing numbers of objects
description: Sal talks about what "more than" and "less than" mean.

title: Compare numbers of objects 1
description: Practice counting which group has more objects.

title: Comparing numbers on the number line
description: Sal uses number line to compare numbers less than or equal to 10.

title: Comparing numbers to 10
description: Practice saying if one number is less than or greater than another number. Numbers are between 0 and 10.

title: Counting by category
description: Sal categorizes objects then count the number of things in each category.

title: Compare numbers of objects 2
description: Practice counting to see which group has the most things in it.

title: Addition and subtraction intro
description: Learn the basics of adding and subtracting.

title: What is addition? What is subtraction?
description: Learn what it means to add. Learn what it means to subtract.

title: Intro to addition
description: Learn what it means to add. The examples used are 1+1 and 2+3.

title: Add within 5
description: Add small numbers. All answers are five or less.

title: Intro to subtraction
description: Sal talks about what it means to subtract. The examples he uses are 4-3 and 5-2.

title: Subtract within 5
description: Subtract small numbers. All answers are less than 5.

title: Making small numbers
description: Learn to make numbers from other numbers by adding. Numbers used are 10 or less.

title: Making 5
description: Learn how to add numbers to make the number five.

title: Making 5
description: Practice adding numbers to make 5.

title: Making small numbers in different ways
description: Practice making a number by adding other numbers. All numbers in these problems are less than 10.

title: Making 10
description: Learn how to make the number 10 from two smaller numbers.

title: Getting to 10 by filling boxes
description: Sal shows how to add two numbers to make 10. He uses 3 + ___ = 10 and 6 + ___ = 10 as examples.

title: Make 10 (grids and number bonds)
description: Practice adding numbers to make 10. These problems show grids to help you out.

title: Adding to 10
description: Sal finds out how many bananas we need to add to 3 bananas to make 10 bananas.

title: Make 10
description: Practice adding numbers to make 10.

title: Put together, take apart
description: When we add, we put together. When we subtract, we take apart. Numbers used are 10 or less.

title: Add and subtract: pieces of fruit
description: Sal adds fruit and subtracts fruit. The examples he uses are 5+3 and 5-3.

title: Addition and subtraction within 10
description: Sal solves addition and subtraction problems with number 10 or less.

title: Add within 10
description: Practice adding by "putting together" (with numbers less than 10).

title: Subtract within 10
description: Practice subtracting by "taking apart" (with numbers less than 10).

title: Relate addition and subtraction
description: Learn how to addition and subtraction are related. Numbers used are 10 or less.

title: Relating addition and subtraction
description: Sal shows the relationship between 2+3=5, 5-2=3, and 5-3=2.

title: Relate addition and subtraction
description: Practice seeing how addition and subtraction are related.

title: Addition and subtraction word problems
description: Learn how to solve addition and subtraction word problems with small numbers. Numbers used are 10 or less.

title: Addition word problems within 10
description: Sal solves word problems by adding small numbers (numbers 10 or less).

title: Addition word problems within 10
description: Practice solving word problems by adding small numbers (numbers 10 or less).

title: Subtraction word problems within 10
description: Sal solves word problems by subtracting small numbers (numbers 10 or less).

title: Subtraction word problems within 10
description: Practice solving word problems by subtracting small numbers (numbers 10 or less).

title: Place value (tens and hundreds)
description: Learn about tens and hundreds. Compare 2-digit and 3-digit numbers.

title: Teens
description: Learn how teen numbers work.

title: Teens as sums with 10
description: Sal looks at the 1 in each teen number and thinks about what it really means.

title: Teen numbers: monkeys
description: Sal breaks the number 18 into 10 and 8.

title: Teen numbers
description: Practice thinking of teen numbers as a ten plus some ones.

title: Tens
description: Learn to see two-digit numbers as tens and ones.

title: Intro to place value
description: Sal uses the number 37 to explain why we use a "ones place" and a "tens place" when writing numbers.

title: Place value example: 25
description: Sal shows 25 as 2 tens and 5 ones.

title: Place value example: 42
description: Sal shows 42 as 4 tens and 2 ones.

title: Groups of ten objects
description: Practice grouping objects by tens.

title: Tens and ones
description: Practice thinking about 2-digit numbers as tens and ones.

title: 2-digit place value challenge
description: Practice breaking numbers apart into tens and ones.

title: Comparing 2-digit numbers
description: Learn how to compare two-digit numbers by thinking about place value (tens and ones).

title: Greater than and less than symbols
description: Greater than and less than symbols can be used to compare numbers and expressions. The greater than symbol is >. So, 9>7 is read as '9 is greater than 7'. The less than symbol is <. Two other comparison symbols are ≥ (greater than or equal to) and ≤ (less than or equal to).

title: Compare 2-digit numbers
description: Practice comparing numbers (within 100) using the symbols <, >, and =.

title: Compare 2-digit numbers 2
description: Practice more challenging problems comparing numbers within 100.

title: Comparison symbols review
description: Review greater than, less than, and equal to symbols and try some practice problems.

title: Hundreds
description: Learn to see three-digit numbers as hundreds, tens, and ones.

title: Hundreds, tens, and ones
description: Practice thinking about place value of 3-digit numbers as hundreds, tens, and ones.

title: 3-digit place value challenge
description: Practice breaking numbers into hundreds, tens, and ones.
